- OKAY.

226
00:08:57,337 --> 00:09:00,107
- WOW. WHO KNEW THAT
WATERCRESS, GARBANZO BEANS,

227
00:09:00,140 --> 00:09:01,875
AND WALNUTS COULD COMPLEMENT
EACH OTHER SO WELL?

228
00:09:01,909 --> 00:09:03,911
- GOOD DRESSING TOO, RIGHT?

229
00:09:03,944 --> 00:09:05,278
FLAXSEED AND AGAVE--

230
00:09:05,312 --> 00:09:07,915
SAME BASIC INGREDIENTS
AS BIRD FEED.

231
00:09:07,948 --> 00:09:09,783
- [sighs]

232
00:09:09,817 --> 00:09:13,053
I'M JUST GONNA COME RIGHT OUT
AND SAY IT.

233
00:09:13,086 --> 00:09:14,922
I WANT TO DEFINE
YOUR BAGUA.

234
00:09:14,955 --> 00:09:18,692
- OKAY. WHAT'S THAT?
- IT'S A FENG SHUI TERM.

235
00:09:18,726 --> 00:09:22,029
THE ENERGY IN THIS HOUSE
IS A LITTLE STALE,

236
00:09:22,062 --> 00:09:24,765
BUT I THINK
I COULD REDEFINE YOUR FLOW

237
00:09:24,798 --> 00:09:27,267
IN A VERY POSITIVE WAY.

238
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:29,637
- GREAT.
I'M NOT REALLY ATTACHED

239
00:09:29,670 --> 00:09:31,238
TO THE WAY THIS STUFF
IS ARRANGED

240
00:09:31,271 --> 00:09:35,142
OR THE STUFF ITSELF
OR THIS HOUSE EVEN, REALLY.

241
00:09:35,175 --> 00:09:36,610
- GREAT.
LET'S DO IT.

242
00:09:36,644 --> 00:09:39,079
- AM I NOT BEING
OBVIOUS ENOUGH?

243
00:09:39,112 --> 00:09:40,948
I FEEL LIKE
I'M BEING OBVIOUS.

244
00:09:40,981 --> 00:09:42,783
- THIS JUST IN.

245
00:09:42,816 --> 00:09:45,085
HARVEST FESTIVAL?
MORE LIKE HARVEST "BESTIVAL."

246
00:09:45,118 --> 00:09:46,987
THE PARKS DEPARTMENT
HAS PLANTED THE SEEDS,

247
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:49,056
AND NOW THEY'RE
HARVESTING THE REWARDS.

248
00:09:49,089 --> 00:09:50,758
- GREAT, YOU DONE?

249
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:52,660
- THEY'LL PUT THE "FUN"
IN FUNNEL CAKE.

250
00:09:52,693 --> 00:09:53,761
OKAY, NOW I'M DONE.

251
00:09:53,794 --> 00:09:55,729
- TELL ME ABOUT BEN WYATT.
- SURE.

252
00:09:55,763 --> 00:09:57,164
HE WORKS
FOR THE STATE GOVERNMENT,

253
00:09:57,197 --> 00:09:59,232
AND HE'S BEEN COMING TO ADVISE
US ABOUT OUR BUDGET.

254
00:09:59,266 --> 00:10:00,701
- OH, COME ON, LESLIE.

255
00:10:00,734 --> 00:10:02,269
THE DOUCHE BLEW THE STORY
WIDE OPEN.

256
00:10:02,302 --> 00:10:04,404
BEN WYATT BANKRUPTS A TOWN
AND THEN COMES TO PAWNEE

257
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:05,906
TO TELL US
HOW TO SPEND OUR MONEY?

258
00:10:05,939 --> 00:10:07,307
- THERE'S
NO STORY HERE, SHAUNA.

259
00:10:07,340 --> 00:10:09,242
HE'S JUST
A DEDICATED CIVIL SERVANT

260
00:10:09,276 --> 00:10:11,111
WHO'S DOING WHATEVER HE CAN
TO MAKE SURE

261
00:10:11,144 --> 00:10:14,782
THAT THIS IS THE BEST
HARVEST FESTIVAL EVER.

262
00:10:14,815 --> 00:10:18,051
AND HE'S EASY ON THE EYES TOO.
[chuckles]

263
00:10:18,085 --> 00:10:20,788
- UM, WHAT EXACTLY IS THE NATURE
OF YOUR RELATIONSHIP WITH HIM?

264
00:10:20,821 --> 00:10:22,690
- STRICTLY PROFESSIONAL,
JUST FRIENDS.

265
00:10:22,723 --> 00:10:23,924
- SO ARE YOU COLLEAGUES,
OR ARE YOU FRIENDS?

266
00:10:23,957 --> 00:10:27,995
- WE ARE COLLEAGUES
WITH BENEFITS.

267
00:10:28,028 --> 00:10:31,098
WE'RE COLLEAGUES
WHO BENEFIT FROM THE FACT

268
00:10:31,131 --> 00:10:32,766
THAT WE'RE ALSO FRIENDS.

269
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:35,803
I'M SORRY, SHAUNA.
I THINK I NEED TO GO.

270
00:10:35,836 --> 00:10:37,270
BUT, UM, THANK YOU
SO MUCH.

271
00:10:37,304 --> 00:10:38,972
AND AS ALWAYS, EVERYTHING
I SAID IS OFF THE RECORD.

272
00:10:39,006 --> 00:10:40,073
OKAY? BYE.

273
00:10:40,107 --> 00:10:42,810
- WHAT'S THE NEXT TASK?

274
00:10:42,843 --> 00:10:44,311
- OH, WE HAVE TO WRITE HER
GRANDMOTHER A THANK-YOU NOTE

275
00:10:44,344 --> 00:10:45,578
FOR A BIRTHDAY CHECK.

276
00:10:45,612 --> 00:10:47,715
IT HAS TO BE REALLY GOOD, TOO,
'CAUSE IT'S FIVE MONTHS LATE.

277
00:10:47,748 --> 00:10:49,316
- NEVER WRITTEN
A THANK-YOU NOTE BEFORE.

278
00:10:49,349 --> 00:10:50,684
THIS WILL BE FUN.

279
00:10:50,718 --> 00:10:52,385
WHAT DOES SHE CALL HER?

280
00:10:52,419 --> 00:10:54,454
- GAMMA.
NO, NANNAW.

281
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:56,356
OR NANNA--
GIZMO.

282
00:10:56,389 --> 00:10:58,225
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

283
00:11:01,161 --> 00:11:03,096
THIS IS FOR YOUR GIZMO.

284
00:11:03,130 --> 00:11:05,733
I THINK YOU'LL FIND
IT'S PRETTY GOOD.

285
00:11:05,766 --> 00:11:07,768
- "DEAR APRIL'S GRANDMOTHER."

286
00:11:07,801 --> 00:11:09,236
I SAID GRANDFATHER.

287
00:11:09,269 --> 00:11:11,805
- OH. OOPS.
OKAY.

288
00:11:11,839 --> 00:11:13,841
- "YOU ARE A BEAUTIFUL
AND AMAZING WOMAN--" MAN.

289
00:11:13,874 --> 00:11:15,876
"I HOPE SOMEDAY I CAN BECOME
HALF THE WOMAN YOU ARE."

290
00:11:15,909 --> 00:11:17,010
HE'S A MAN.

291
00:11:17,044 --> 00:11:18,145
"THANK YOU FOR THE $500."

292
00:11:18,178 --> 00:11:19,312
IT WAS $5.

293
00:11:19,346 --> 00:11:21,048
"ENJOY THE MOUSE RAT CD."

294
00:11:21,081 --> 00:11:24,017
HE IS DEAF.

295
00:11:24,051 --> 00:11:27,755
- OKAY, DO YOU WANT ME TO MAKE
THOSE CHANGES, OR IS IT GOOD?

296
00:11:27,788 --> 00:11:29,089
- BEFORE WE DO
THIS NEXT INTERVIEW,

297
00:11:29,122 --> 00:11:30,991
THERE'S A LITTLE SECRET
I WANT TO LET YOU IN ON.

298
00:11:31,024 --> 00:11:33,293
IT'S CALLED
THE HAVERFORD SCHMOOZE.

299
00:11:33,326 --> 00:11:34,862
- I WAS JUST CAUGHT OFF GUARD.
I'M FINE.

300
00:11:34,895 --> 00:11:36,063
- THREE EASY STEPS--

301
00:11:36,096 --> 00:11:37,765
SMILE...

302
00:11:37,798 --> 00:11:41,268
FRIENDLY PHYSICAL CONTACT,
AND FLATTERY.

303
00:11:41,301 --> 00:11:44,237
HEY, PERD, IS YOUR DAD ROBOCOP?
'CAUSE YOU'RE ARMS ARE GUNS.

304
00:11:44,271 --> 00:11:46,273
- ROBOCOP DIDN'T HAVE
GUNS FOR ARMS.

305
00:11:46,306 --> 00:11:48,408
- OH, MY GOD. THAT'S SO
NOT THE POINT, YOU NERD.

306
00:11:48,441 --> 00:11:50,878
- I'M JUST SAYING.
WHY ARE WE GOING TO A MALL?

307
00:11:50,911 --> 00:11:52,813
- I'M GETTING YOU A NEW SUIT.

308
00:11:52,846 --> 00:11:54,281
I'VE LET THIS GO ON
LONG ENOUGH.

309
00:11:54,314 --> 00:11:56,449
- I LIKE THIS SUIT.
- YOU SHOULDN'T...

310
00:11:56,483 --> 00:11:58,451
'CAUSE IT LOOKS LIKE GARBAGE.

311
00:11:58,485 --> 00:12:00,854
- YOUR SUIT LOOKS
MORE LIKE GARBAGE.

312
00:12:00,888 --> 00:12:01,989
- OH, REALLY?
- YEAH.

313
00:12:02,022 --> 00:12:04,491
- 'CAUSE BROOKS BROTHERS BOYS
DOESN'T MAKE GARBAGE.

314
00:12:04,524 --> 00:12:07,828
- OKAY, THIS NEXT THING IS
A PHOTOGRAPHY-CLASS ASSIGNMENT.

315
00:12:07,861 --> 00:12:08,762
CAN YOU FIGURE THAT OUT?

316
00:12:08,796 --> 00:12:11,799
- "ENCAPSULATE THE SPIRIT
OF MELANCHOLY."

317
00:12:11,832 --> 00:12:13,266
- MELANCHOLY.
- GIVE ME THIS.

318
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:14,534
EASY.

319
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:16,536
BOOM--A SAD DESK.

320
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:19,773
BOOM--SAD WALL.

321
00:12:19,807 --> 00:12:22,275
IT'S ART.
ANYTHING IS ANYTHING.

322
00:12:22,309 --> 00:12:23,877
- OH, RIGHT ON.

323
00:12:23,911 --> 00:12:25,145
UH, I'M GONNA GO DROP THIS OFF
AND PICK UP THE MAIL.

324
00:12:25,178 --> 00:12:27,781
- SAD FLOOR.

325
00:12:27,815 --> 00:12:30,283
- IT DOES LOOK SAD...
KIND OF.

326
00:12:30,317 --> 00:12:33,821
SORRY FOR STEPPING
ON YOU, FLOOR.

327
00:12:33,854 --> 00:12:35,155
[door opens, closes

328
00:12:36,323 --> 00:12:37,825
- HEY.

329
00:12:37,858 --> 00:12:39,259
YOU GOT ANDY
DOING ALL YOUR WORK FOR YOU?

330
00:12:39,292 --> 00:12:41,962
- YES. BUT HE SAID
HE WANTED TO DO IT.

331
00:12:41,995 --> 00:12:43,797
I'M ONLY DOING IT
BECAUSE I'M GETTING--

332
00:12:43,831 --> 00:12:44,898
- YEAH, I DON'T CARE.

333
00:12:44,932 --> 00:12:46,466
I GOT SOMETHING TO ADD
TO YOUR LIST.

334
00:12:46,499 --> 00:12:49,569
YEP.
THERE WE GO.

335
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:51,271
THAT'S THE STUFF.

336
00:12:51,304 --> 00:12:53,974
- APRIL REALLY DOES THIS
EVERY DAY?

337
00:12:54,007 --> 00:12:55,976
- YES.
WORK THE HEEL.

338
00:12:56,009 --> 00:12:57,310
- ANDY, CAN I BE NEXT?

339
00:12:57,344 --> 00:12:59,279
- YEAH.

340
00:12:59,312 --> 00:13:02,515
- I'VE GOT A CORN SO BIG
YOU COULD SLAP BUTTER ON IT.

341
00:13:02,549 --> 00:13:05,285
- WELCOME
TO YA' HEARD WITH PERD.

342
00:13:05,318 --> 00:13:06,820
I'M PERD HAPLEY.

343
00:13:06,854 --> 00:13:08,588
THE STORY OF OUR GUESTS TODAY
IS THAT THEY ARE

344
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:10,590
FROM THE DEPARTMENT
OF PARKS AND RECREATION--

345
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:12,392
BEN WYATT AND TOM HAVERFORD.

346
00:13:12,425 --> 00:13:14,561
- WHAT UP, PERD?
BIG FAN.

347
00:13:14,594 --> 00:13:17,397
- ME TOO, PERD.
WHAT UP?

348
00:13:17,430 --> 00:13:19,066
- THE THING ABOUT
THIS FIRST QUESTION IS--

349
00:13:19,099 --> 00:13:21,468
I'D LIKE TO ASK YOU
ABOUT THE HARVEST FESTIVAL.

350
00:13:21,501 --> 00:13:23,470
- PERD,
IT'S GONNA BE AMAZING--

351
00:13:23,503 --> 00:13:24,637
CARNIVAL RIDES, GAMES.

352
00:13:24,671 --> 00:13:28,208
SWEETUMS IS EVEN BUILDING
A PLUS-SIZED ROLLER COASTER

353
00:13:28,241 --> 00:13:30,577
FOR SOME OF PAWNEE'S OBESE
THRILL SEEKERS.

354
00:13:30,610 --> 00:13:32,112
YOU MUST BE THIS WIDE TO RIDE.

355
00:13:32,145 --> 00:13:34,982
- WOW. THAT'S GONNA BE
A PRETTY BIG ROLLER COASTER.

356
00:13:35,015 --> 00:13:36,950
- YEP.

357
00:13:36,984 --> 00:13:38,451
- HEY, GUYS, HOW'D IT GO?

358
00:13:38,485 --> 00:13:40,453
- WELL, THERE WERE
SOME STICKY MOMENTS.

359
00:13:40,487 --> 00:13:42,622
- LET'S GO
TO THE VIDEOTAPE.

360
00:13:42,655 --> 00:13:44,624
- AH! LOOK...

361
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:46,459
WHO HASN'T HAD GAY THOUGHTS?

362
00:13:46,493 --> 00:13:47,394
WHO?

363
00:13:47,427 --> 00:13:49,029
- YOU OKAY?
- YEAH, I'M FINE, I'M FINE.

364
00:13:49,062 --> 00:13:50,363
I MEAN, YOU KNOW,
SOMETIMES I FEEL LIKE

365
00:13:50,397 --> 00:13:51,531
I MIGHT NEED GLASSES.

366
00:13:51,564 --> 00:13:54,134
IS THERE A BIRD IN HERE?

367
00:13:54,167 --> 00:13:56,603
I SWEAR I KEEP SEEING A BIRD
IN THE STUDIO.

368
00:13:56,636 --> 00:13:58,138
- HOW DID THIS HAPPEN?

369
00:13:58,171 --> 00:13:59,606
- HE WAS FINE UNTIL PERD
STARTED ASKING HIM

370
00:13:59,639 --> 00:14:01,208
ABOUT THE BOY-MAYOR STUFF.

371
00:14:01,241 --> 00:14:03,310
- WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?
YOU LOOK PSYCHOTIC.

372
00:14:03,343 --> 00:14:05,612
- I WAS 18
WHEN I WAS ELECTED MAYOR, OKAY?

373
00:14:05,645 --> 00:14:07,981
SO EXCUSE ME FOR THAT.

374
00:14:08,015 --> 00:14:10,117
CINDY ECKERT HAD JUST TURNED ME
DOWN FOR SENIOR PROM.

375
00:14:10,150 --> 00:14:11,952
DO YOU KNOW HOW THAT FEEL--
I SHOULD CALL HER.

376
00:14:11,985 --> 00:14:13,586
I SHOULD. I--
NO, I SHOULDN'T.

377
00:14:13,620 --> 00:14:16,890
AND I'M NOT GOING TO, AND
I'M PROUD OF MYSELF FOR THAT.

378
00:14:16,924 --> 00:14:19,626
- AND THEN HE TALKED
ABOUT FEELING UP CINDY ECKERT

379
00:14:19,659 --> 00:14:21,962
FOR THE FIRST TIME
FOR ABOUT FIVE MINUTES.

380
00:14:21,995 --> 00:14:23,630
AND THEN THE SHOW ENDED...

381
00:14:23,663 --> 00:14:26,133
AS DID OUR CAREERS
AND PROBABLY HARVEST FEST.

382
00:14:26,166 --> 00:14:27,901
[camera shutter clicks]

383
00:14:27,935 --> 00:14:30,570
- BOOM--SADNESS.
THAT'S THE ONE.

384
00:14:34,574 --> 00:14:35,976
- NATALIE. HEY.

385
00:14:36,009 --> 00:14:37,210
IT'S ME, ANDY.

386
00:14:37,244 --> 00:14:39,312
- YOU'RE
AN HOUR AND HALF LATE.

387
00:14:39,346 --> 00:14:40,380
- I KNOW. I KNOW.

388
00:14:40,413 --> 00:14:42,315
I HAD TO MASSAGE
A TON OF FEET--

389
00:14:42,349 --> 00:14:43,550
SUPER SORRY.

390
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:46,019
COME ON, GET IN. I-I NEED TO DO
EVERYTHING ON APRIL'S LIST,

391
00:14:46,053 --> 00:14:47,654
OR SHE'S NOT GONNA
GO OUT WITH ME.

392
00:14:47,687 --> 00:14:49,589
- YOU'RE INTO APRIL?

393
00:14:49,622 --> 00:14:51,124
- AH.
COME ON.

394
00:14:51,158 --> 00:14:52,692
WE'LL TALK ABOUT IT
IN THE CAR.

395
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:54,327
- HOLD ON.
I'LL GET MY BOOKS.

396
00:14:54,361 --> 00:14:55,963
- OKAY.

397
00:14:55,996 --> 00:14:58,231
- OKAY, GREAT.
CALL ME.

398
00:14:58,265 --> 00:15:00,934
THAT SHOULD BE
SOME DAMAGE CONTROL.

399
00:15:00,968 --> 00:15:02,235
I'M HAVING DINNER
WITH PERD HAPLEY.

400
00:15:02,269 --> 00:15:03,436
TOM, WHAT DO WE HAVE?

401
00:15:03,470 --> 00:15:05,372
- I'VE GOTTEN CALLS
FROM A DOZEN BUSINESSES

402
00:15:05,405 --> 00:15:06,706
THINKING ABOUT PULLING
THEIR SPONSORSHIPS.

403
00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:08,375
SWEETUMS MIGHT CANCEL
THE FAT-COASTER.

404
00:15:08,408 --> 00:15:09,442
- OH, MY GOD.

405
00:15:09,476 --> 00:15:10,577
OKAY, LOOK, WE NEED TO FOCUS.

406
00:15:10,610 --> 00:15:12,980
WE STILL HAVE
THE PAWNEE TODAY INTERVIEW.

407
00:15:13,013 --> 00:15:14,347
- WELL, IS IT TOO LATE
TO CANCEL?

408
00:15:14,381 --> 00:15:17,384
- YEAH, YEAH,
IT'S TOO LATE TO CANCEL.

409
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:19,519
JOAN CALLAMEZZO RUNS
THIS TOWN.

410
00:15:19,552 --> 00:15:20,954
BUT, BEN,
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

411
00:15:20,988 --> 00:15:22,022
YOU'RE NOT GOING
IN FRONT OF THE CAMERA.

412
00:15:22,055 --> 00:15:23,690
- FINE WITH ME.

413
00:15:23,723 --> 00:15:25,692
- ARE YOU TRYING TO LURE
THIS YOUNG LADY INTO YOUR VAN?

414
00:15:25,725 --> 00:15:27,527
- YEAH.

415
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:29,662
BUT SHE'S BEING
REALLY DIFFICULT ABOUT IT.

416
00:15:29,696 --> 00:15:32,032
UH, AND IT'S ACTUALLY
NOT MY VAN.

417
00:15:32,065 --> 00:15:34,034
UH, I STOLE IT
FROM A FRIEND OF MINE.

418
00:15:34,067 --> 00:15:35,635
I TECHNICALLY
SHOULDN'T BE EVEN DRIVING,

419
00:15:35,668 --> 00:15:39,406
BECAUSE, UH, MY LICENSE
IS CRAZY EXPIRED.

420
00:15:39,439 --> 00:15:40,573
[chuckles]

421
00:15:40,607 --> 00:15:42,075
- THAT'S, UH, DWYER.

422
00:15:42,109 --> 00:15:44,544
D-W-Y-E-R.

423
00:15:44,577 --> 00:15:45,678
- OH, DUDE!

424
00:15:45,712 --> 00:15:48,115
COME ON,
I GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE!

425
00:15:48,148 --> 00:15:50,683
NATALIE, TELL THIS GUY
YOU KNOW ME.

426
00:15:50,717 --> 00:15:53,520
- [laughs]

427
00:15:53,553 --> 00:15:54,454
- JOAN!

428
00:15:54,487 --> 00:15:56,656
OH, I THOUGHT
YOU WERE JENNIFER ANISTON

429
00:15:56,689 --> 00:15:58,358
FILMING A MOVIE HERE.

430
00:15:58,391 --> 00:15:59,626
[both laugh]

431
00:15:59,659 --> 00:16:01,428
JOAN, LET'S MAKE
A PACT, OKAY?

432
00:16:01,461 --> 00:16:04,031
IF WE'RE BOTH STILL SINGLE
IN AN HOUR, LET'S GET MARRIED.

433
00:16:04,064 --> 00:16:05,765
- TOM, I'M ALREADY MARRIED.

434
00:16:05,798 --> 00:16:07,267
- OH, THAT'S RIGHT, TO SEAL.

435
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:09,136
OH, I CONFUSED YOU
WITH HEIDI KLUM AGAIN.

436
00:16:09,169 --> 00:16:11,738
- OH!
- SEE YOU LATER, JOAN.

437
00:16:11,771 --> 00:16:13,573
THAT'S HOW IT'S DONE.
[Joan laughing]

438
00:16:13,606 --> 00:16:15,108
- OKAY, FIVE, FOUR...

439
00:16:15,142 --> 00:16:18,045
- HELLO, AND WELCOME
TO PAWNEE TODAY.

440
00:16:18,078 --> 00:16:19,679
I'M JOAN CALLAMEZZO.

441
00:16:19,712 --> 00:16:21,714
TODAY'S GUEST IS LESLIE KNOPE,

442
00:16:21,748 --> 00:16:24,217
WHO IS HERE TO TELL US
HOW THIS YEAR'S HARVEST FESTIVAL

443
00:16:24,251 --> 00:16:26,386
IS GOING TO BANKRUPT THE CITY.

444
00:16:26,419 --> 00:16:28,355
- WELL, JOAN, ACTUALLY,
THERE'S A LOT

445
00:16:28,388 --> 00:16:30,357
OF FALSE INFORMATION
FLYING AROUND.

446
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:32,592
THE HARVEST FESTIVAL IS--
- JUST JUMPING RIGHT IN.

447
00:16:32,625 --> 00:16:33,793
THAT'S RUDE.

448
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:35,528
- I JUST WANT EVERYONE TO KNOW

449
00:16:35,562 --> 00:16:37,397
WHAT AN EXTRAORDINARY EVENT
THIS IS GOING TO BE.

450
00:16:37,430 --> 00:16:39,632
- BUT AT WHAT COST?

451
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:42,535
HOW MANY CITIES
DOES BEN WYATT NEED TO DESTROY

452
00:16:42,569 --> 00:16:44,471
BEFORE HE'S PUT BEHIND BARS?

453
00:16:44,504 --> 00:16:46,039
- BEN WYATT
HAS DONE NOTHING WRONG.

454
00:16:46,073 --> 00:16:49,576
YOU KNOW, IF YOU WANT TO ASK
HIM QUESTIONS,

455
00:16:49,609 --> 00:16:50,643
LET'S GO FOR IT, HUH?

456
00:16:50,677 --> 00:16:52,712
JUST ASK ANY QUESTION
ABOUT HIS PAST OR PRESENT.

457
00:16:52,745 --> 00:16:54,514
JUST GET IT OVER WITH.
BEN, LET'S GET UP HERE.

458
00:16:54,547 --> 00:16:56,416
YEAH, YEAH, COME ON.

459
00:16:56,449 --> 00:16:57,650
WE'LL JUST ASK HIM
A BUNCH OF QUESTIONS,

460
00:16:57,684 --> 00:16:59,752
AND THEN WE'LL GET EVERYTHING
CLEARED AND OUT OF THE WAY.

461
00:16:59,786 --> 00:17:01,054
SOUND GOOD?
YEAH?

462
00:17:01,088 --> 00:17:02,189
- GREAT.
- GOOD.

463
00:17:02,222 --> 00:17:03,790
UH, LET'S TAKE
SOME CALLS, JOAN.

464
00:17:03,823 --> 00:17:05,158
- WHY DON'T YOU?

465
00:17:05,192 --> 00:17:06,626
- OKAY.
UH, CALLER, ARE YOU THERE?

466
00:17:06,659 --> 00:17:09,729
- YEAH, HOW CAN YOU JUSTIFY
RAISING TAXES

467
00:17:09,762 --> 00:17:12,332
FOR SOMETHING
THAT WILL HURT THE TOWN?

468
00:17:12,365 --> 00:17:15,568
- I...

469
00:17:15,602 --> 00:17:17,704
FOR...

470
00:17:17,737 --> 00:17:20,773
- UH, JUST TO ADD
TO WHAT BEN'S STAMMERING ABOUT,

471
00:17:20,807 --> 00:17:23,243
UM, WE AREN'T GOING
TO RAISE TAXES,

472
00:17:23,276 --> 00:17:25,678
SO THAT'S THAT.
[chuckles]

473
00:17:25,712 --> 00:17:27,046
NEXT CALLER.

474
00:17:28,415 --> 00:17:30,683
- DO YOU FISH, APRIL?

475
00:17:30,717 --> 00:17:32,652
- NO.
FISH ARE GROSS.

476
00:17:32,685 --> 00:17:34,587
- LET ME GIVE YOU
A PIECE OF FISHING ADVICE.

477
00:17:34,621 --> 00:17:35,755
- I SAID I DON'T--

478
00:17:35,788 --> 00:17:36,856
- WHEN YOU HAVE A FISH
ON THE LINE,

479
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:38,425
YOU DON'T JUST DRAG IT
BEHIND THE BOAT.

480
00:17:38,458 --> 00:17:41,561
YOU EITHER REEL IT IN,
OR YOU CUT HIM LOOSE,

481
00:17:41,594 --> 00:17:43,663
ESPECIALLY
IF HE'S A NICE FISH

482
00:17:43,696 --> 00:17:45,432
WITH A BIG,
LOVABLE FISH HEART.

483
00:17:45,465 --> 00:17:47,367
- YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

484
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:50,637
- MAYBE NOT.
MAYBE YOU REALLY DO HATE ANDY.

485
00:17:50,670 --> 00:17:54,241
MAYBE MOVING TO INDIANAPOLIS
JUST TO GET REVENGE ON HIM

486
00:17:54,274 --> 00:17:56,576
IS A REALLY GOOD IDEA.

487
00:17:56,609 --> 00:17:59,146
WHAT DO I KNOW?

488
00:17:59,179 --> 00:18:02,782
[cell phone rings, vibrates]

489
00:18:05,552 --> 00:18:07,620
- YOU ARE GOING TO LOVE THIS.

490
00:18:07,654 --> 00:18:11,124
VEROSIAN TEA REALLY SUPERCHARGES
THE BACTERIA IN YOUR COLON.

491
00:18:11,158 --> 00:18:13,393
PLUS, IT SMELLS INTERESTING.
WAFT IT.

492
00:18:13,426 --> 00:18:15,728
- ARE WE ACTUALLY EVER
GONNA DRINK IT,

493
00:18:15,762 --> 00:18:17,364
OR WE'RE JUST GONNA SNIFF IT?

494
00:18:17,397 --> 00:18:19,399
I LOVE SNIFFING.
DON'T GET ME WRONG.

495
00:18:19,432 --> 00:18:22,369
- YOU ARE HILARIOUS.

496
00:18:22,402 --> 00:18:24,437
- SO YOU'RE LEAVING SOON.

497
00:18:24,471 --> 00:18:26,806
- UM, BACK
TO INDIANAPOLIS BRIEFLY

498
00:18:26,839 --> 00:18:29,276
AND THEN ON TO A TOWN
CALLED SNERLING, INDIANA,

499
00:18:29,309 --> 00:18:30,443
FOR SEVERAL MONTHS.

500
00:18:30,477 --> 00:18:31,644
- NEVER HEARD OF IT.

501
00:18:31,678 --> 00:18:33,180
- IT'S QUITE SMALL.

502
00:18:33,213 --> 00:18:35,182
THE COWS OUTNUMBER THE PEOPLE
40 TO 1.

503
00:18:35,215 --> 00:18:37,217
IT SOUNDS AMAZING.

504
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:38,885
- I LIKE YOU A LOT.

505
00:18:38,918 --> 00:18:42,189
I LOVE SPENDING TIME
WITH YOU.

506
00:18:42,222 --> 00:18:44,757
- AND I THOROUGHLY
ENJOY YOU, ANN PERKINS.

507
00:18:44,791 --> 00:18:48,728
- I JUST THINK WE NEED TO TALK
ABOUT WHAT THAT MEANS FOR US.

508
00:18:48,761 --> 00:18:50,430
I DON'T WANT TO BE CLINGY.
I--

509
00:18:50,463 --> 00:18:52,432
- PLEASE, IT IS SOMETHING
THAT WE NEED TO FIGURE OUT,

510
00:18:52,465 --> 00:18:54,534
AND WE SHOULD DO THAT
RIGHT NOW.

511
00:18:54,567 --> 00:18:58,705
- I'M SO HAPPY YOU SAID THAT.

512
00:18:58,738 --> 00:19:00,573
WOW, THAT'S DISGUSTING.

513
00:19:00,607 --> 00:19:03,843
- YES, IT'S VERY HARD
TO DRINK.

514
00:19:05,645 --> 00:19:07,680
- YEAH, WHY SHOULD WE TRUST
THIS BEN WYATT GUY?

515
00:19:07,714 --> 00:19:09,716
- BECAUSE I'M TRUSTY.

516
00:19:09,749 --> 00:19:11,718
TRUST ME.
I'M TRUSTWORTHY.

517
00:19:11,751 --> 00:19:16,256
AND I AM WORKING
VERY HARD TO...

518
00:19:16,289 --> 00:19:19,559
[sighs] MAKE SURE THAT THIS TOWN
GETS BACK ON ITS FEET.

519
00:19:19,592 --> 00:19:20,960
- THERE WE GO.
OKAY, GREAT.

520
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:22,295
NEXT CALLER.

521
00:19:22,329 --> 00:19:23,896
- SO I LOOKED YOU UP
ON ALTAVISTA,

522
00:19:23,930 --> 00:19:25,765
AND I FOUND OUT
THAT THE LAST SEVEN TOWNS

523
00:19:25,798 --> 00:19:27,734
YOU'VE GONE TO
ENDED UP BANKRUPT.

524
00:19:27,767 --> 00:19:29,202
- OKAY, FIRST OF ALL,

525
00:19:29,236 --> 00:19:32,439
WHY DOES EVERYONE IN THIS TOWN
USE ALTAVISTA?

526
00:19:32,472 --> 00:19:34,541
IS IT 1997?

527
00:19:34,574 --> 00:19:36,776
AND SECOND,
I AM A BUDGET SPECIALIST.

528
00:19:36,809 --> 00:19:39,646
I WENT TO THOSE TOWNS
BECAUSE THEY WERE BANKRUPT,

529
00:19:39,679 --> 00:19:41,581
AND NOW THEY AREN'T.

530
00:19:41,614 --> 00:19:43,616
AND, YEAH, I SCREWED UP
WHEN I WAS 18,

531
00:19:43,650 --> 00:19:46,753
BUT WHO DOESN'T DO DUMB STUFF
WHEN THEY'RE 18?

532
00:19:46,786 --> 00:19:48,721
JOAN?
- I STOLE MY...

533
00:19:48,755 --> 00:19:51,991
[clears throat]
GYM TEACHER'S HUSBAND.

534
00:19:52,024 --> 00:19:54,727
- SO THERE YOU GO.

535
00:19:54,761 --> 00:19:57,797
- WELL, WHAT ELSE
DO YOU GOT, CALLERS?

536
00:19:57,830 --> 00:19:58,498
GOING ONCE, GOING TWI--

537
00:19:58,531 --> 00:20:00,933
OH, HERE WE GO.
- YEAH, HI.

538
00:20:00,967 --> 00:20:02,769
UM, CAN YOU TELL ME MORE
ABOUT THE CORN MAZE

539
00:20:02,802 --> 00:20:03,903
AT THE HARVEST FESTIVAL?

540
00:20:03,936 --> 00:20:05,572
ARE DOGS ALLOWED?

541
00:20:08,575 --> 00:20:10,243
- HELLO.
- HELLO.

542
00:20:10,277 --> 00:20:11,744
- HOW DID IT GO TODAY?

543
00:20:11,778 --> 00:20:12,945
- IT WAS SUPER FUN.

544
00:20:12,979 --> 00:20:14,681
- IT WAS?
- YEAH.

545
00:20:14,714 --> 00:20:16,883
DO YOU HAVE A LIST
FOR TOMORROW?

546
00:20:16,916 --> 00:20:18,585
- [scoffs]

547
00:20:18,618 --> 00:20:20,420
YOU WANT TO DO THIS AGAIN
TOMORROW?

548
00:20:20,453 --> 00:20:21,888
- YES, I DO.
I MEAN, THAT'S THE DEAL, RIGHT?

549
00:20:21,921 --> 00:20:23,456
I GOT TO DO IT
FOR A WHOLE MONTH

550
00:20:23,490 --> 00:20:27,260
AND THEN YOU'RE NOT GONNA MOVE
TO INDIANAPOLIS--

551
00:20:33,466 --> 00:20:35,302
- I BETTER BE THE ONLY PERSON
YOU KISSED TODAY.

552
00:20:35,335 --> 00:20:37,270
- I AM...

553
00:20:37,304 --> 00:20:39,339
I'M POSITIVE THAT YOU ARE.

554
00:20:42,975 --> 00:20:44,076
- [chuckles]
IF I THOUGHT YOU WERE SERIOUS,

555
00:20:44,110 --> 00:20:45,978
I'D BE OFFENDED, PERD,
BUT I KNOW THAT WE'RE BUDDIES,

556
00:20:46,012 --> 00:20:46,946
AND I KNOW
YOU WOULDN'T DO THAT TO ME.

557
00:20:46,979 --> 00:20:50,317
BUT, NO, THIS IS A BIRTHMARK,
PERD, OKAY?

558
00:20:50,350 --> 00:20:52,285
THIS IS THE LITTLE SCAR I GOT
WHEN I WAS NINE

559
00:20:52,319 --> 00:20:55,955
AND I FELL OFF MY BIKE,
SO, NO, I'M NOT PERFECT!

560
00:20:55,988 --> 00:20:58,325
- I CAN'T LOOK AWAY.
- IT'S A--IT'S AMAZING.

561
00:20:58,358 --> 00:20:59,959
- OKAY, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, NO.
HERE'S THE BEST PART.

562
00:20:59,992 --> 00:21:03,463
- OKAY, UH, THAT'S ALL THE TIME
WE HAVE HERE ON YA' HEARD.

563
00:21:03,496 --> 00:21:05,632
I'M PERD HAPLEY,
CHANNEL 4.

564
00:21:05,665 --> 00:21:08,368
- [scoffs]
MORE LIKE "TURD CRAPLEY."

565
00:21:08,401 --> 00:21:09,836
- YES, YES.
- YEAH?

566
00:21:09,869 --> 00:21:09,936
- BRAVO.
- THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

